                <head>240. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>At the 316th meeting of the National Security Council, March 14, Director of
                    Central Intelligence <persName corresp="#p_DAW1">Allen Dulles</persName> briefed
                    the Council on developments in Poland: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“<persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> pointed out that <persName
                                corresp="#p_GW1">Gomulka</persName> gave every appearance of putting
                            the brakes on the anti-Stalinist liberalization movement in Poland.
                                <persName corresp="#p_GW1">Gomulka</persName>’s moves were probably
                            dictated by tactics, but there was danger that these tactics would cost
                            him a large measure of popular support. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_DJF1"
                                >Dulles</persName> indicated that Poland’s basic problem was still
                            economic. <persName corresp="#p_GW1">Gomulka</persName> regards the
                            current negotiations with the United <pb facs="0621" n="591"
                                xml:id="pg_591"/> States for assistance as of the utmost importance.
                            If Poland received no assistance from the United States, Mr. <persName
                                corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> predicted that the chances of
                            survival for the <persName corresp="#p_GW1">Gomulka</persName> regime
                            would be very slim indeed. In this contingency, <persName
                                corresp="#p_GW1">Gomulka</persName> would be obliged to turn to the
                            USSR for economic assistance denied him by the United States, and he
                            would therefore be at the mercy of the Soviet Union.” (Memorandum of
                            discussion by <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Gleason</persName>, March 15;
                                <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> Library, Whitman
                            File, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Records)</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
            </div>
